  <span id="freeText9176794561278534131" style="display:none">Imagine it's a rainy night, and you and your best friend are sitting in comfy chairs in front of a fire. Maybe you're drinking hot chocolate, laughing about something when she turns to you and says, "Did I ever tell you the story about David Power and Clare O'Brien from Catlebay?"<br /><br />When you say no, you both settle back and she begins to tell you the story. That's what this book feels like, and it's wonderful.<br /><br />Maeve Binchy is a first class story teller, and ECHOES is one of her best. If you pick it up, you will not be disappointed.</span>
