<div id="review_3831594254" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3831594254" />
    <a title="Stefanie Onieal" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8663809-stefanie-onieal"><img alt="Stefanie Onieal" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3831594254?book_show_action=true">Feb 11, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stefanie Onieal" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stefanie Onieal" href="/user/show/8663809-stefanie-onieal">Stefanie Onieal</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3831594254" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17043107679779021779">I read this when it first came out and I was obsessed with everything Irish. I bought it for my kindle and have spent every spare second of the last few days rereading it. It’s the best of Binchy’s books. She really captured the sexism, repression, and oppression of the Church in 1950s/60s Ireland.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


