<div id="review_1222418582" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1222418582" />
    <a title="Kara Hansen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10572178-kara-hansen"><img alt="Kara Hansen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1561226131p2/10572178.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1222418582?book_show_action=true">Jul 05, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kara Hansen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kara Hansen" href="/user/show/10572178-kara-hansen">Kara Hansen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780099498650" href="/book/show/41957.Echoes">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1222418582" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9388759887788062315">3.5 stars. I have long been a fan of Maeve Binchy, but was finding that I was not enjoying her later written books as much as I had enjoyed her earlier works. <b>Echoes</b> had been sitting on my shelf for quite sometime, and having noted that it was written in 1985, was hoping this would take me back to loving Maeve Binchy. I was certainly not disappointed, and glad I took this on, despite its over 700 page length! This story takes us from 1950 through to 1962 in Castlebay, Ireland. A small seaside vi</span>
  <span id="freeText9388759887788062315" style="display:none">3.5 stars. I have long been a fan of Maeve Binchy, but was finding that I was not enjoying her later written books as much as I had enjoyed her earlier works. <b>Echoes</b> had been sitting on my shelf for quite sometime, and having noted that it was written in 1985, was hoping this would take me back to loving Maeve Binchy. I was certainly not disappointed, and glad I took this on, despite its over 700 page length! This story takes us from 1950 through to 1962 in Castlebay, Ireland. A small seaside village, where of course everyone knows everyone's business. We follow the O'Briens, the Powers, the Doyles and the Dillons as life happens and things do not always go as planned. There are some comical characters, the down and outs, the nosy neighbours~ all of course who mean so well. This was a charming and cozy story, but I did find the last part of the book fell a bit flat as one of the side characters suddenly became central to the wrap up of the book. It came across as odd, almost as though she threw it in to make the story come to a close. Still, delightful Binchy, and I'm glad I saved it on my shelf.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9388759887788062315" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


