<div id="review_2353997279" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2353997279" />
    <a title="Roberta" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5305130-roberta"><img alt="Roberta" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1333819771p2/5305130.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2353997279?book_show_action=true">Apr 26, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Roberta" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Roberta" href="/user/show/5305130-roberta">Roberta</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/6567851-echoes">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5305130-roberta?shelf=ireland">ireland</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5305130-roberta?shelf=religion">religion</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5305130-roberta?shelf=female-author">female-author</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5305130-roberta?shelf=2018">2018</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2353997279" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5720062210460052536">I am now a fan of this author and will surely pick up more of her books! <br/><br/>It is not a short book nor a quick read, but is so emotional in so many ways that you nearly want to cry at one time or another for most of the characters! You will also likely find yourself genuinely caring about the people who you will spend years getting to know—years of their lives, not years spent reading this book : ) —and hoping that they eventually get what they deserve: good or bad. It is sad, it is heartwarming, a</span>
  <span id="freeText5720062210460052536" style="display:none">I am now a fan of this author and will surely pick up more of her books! <br /><br />It is not a short book nor a quick read, but is so emotional in so many ways that you nearly want to cry at one time or another for most of the characters! You will also likely find yourself genuinely caring about the people who you will spend years getting to know—years of their lives, not years spent reading this book : ) —and hoping that they eventually get what they deserve: good or bad. It is sad, it is heartwarming, and it is a worthy book to undertake. <br /><br />I also felt compelled to add it to my 'religion' shelf, as it is clear that the religion in the southern part of Ireland is a <i>significant</i> aspect of their lives. This is the second book where Catholicism has played a major part in the story. The first was a history of Ireland and both that book (<i>Ireland: A Novel</i> by Frank Delaney—also very good!) and this one spent a great deal of time pondering and describing the Catholic faith and what it means to the people of Ireland. As I am not a Catholic, I do not understand the depth to which that religion drives their followers. This is not a criticism, it is just not something that I've been exposed to in my life or faith. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="5720062210460052536" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


