<span id="freeTextContainer15686358346101590124">4/2018 This must be one of the first books by Maeve Binchy that I ever read, which makes sense since it&apos;s one of the first she wrote. I don&apos;t remember this one very well but I&apos;m going to give a 4 star rating all the same because I&apos;ve been collecting them ever since and now have most of them.<br/><br/>5/28/2018 I based my initial 4 star rating on how I feel in general about Binchy books. Now that I&apos;ve re-read it I&apos;m perhaps more critical of this particular one. It might be a mood thing. Anyway, it&apos;s a book</span>
  <span id="freeText15686358346101590124" style="display:none">4/2018 This must be one of the first books by Maeve Binchy that I ever read, which makes sense since it's one of the first she wrote. I don't remember this one very well but I'm going to give a 4 star rating all the same because I've been collecting them ever since and now have most of them.<br /><br />5/28/2018 I based my initial 4 star rating on how I feel in general about Binchy books. Now that I've re-read it I'm perhaps more critical of this particular one. It might be a mood thing. Anyway, it's a book worth reading but it's difficult. The characters are not always likable but they are always human and real. That is true of all Binchy's books and one of the main reasons I keep reading them.<br /><br /></span>
